uk.ac.ed.epcc.webapp.jdbc.expr

Interface IndexedSQLValue<T,I extends DataObject>

  • Type Parameters:
    T - Type of owning/home table.
    I - Type of remote table
    All Superinterfaces:
    FilterProvider<T,IndexedReference<I>>, SQLValue<IndexedReference<I>>, Targetted<IndexedReference<I>>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AbstractSelfSQLValue, CompositeIndexedSQLValue, ConstIndexedSQLValue, IndexedFieldValue, SelfSQLValue, TupleSelfSQLValue

    public interface IndexedSQLValue<T,I extends DataObject>
extends SQLValue<IndexedReference<I>>, FilterProvider<T,IndexedReference<I>>
    A SQLValue that generates a IndexedReference to a remote table. This also supports the necessary methods to join through to the remote table.
    Author:
    spb
    See Also:
    DerefSQLExpression, RemoteSQLValue
